'''''At a Window in the Artist's Studio''''' is a drawing by the Danish painter, [[C. W. Eckersberg]]. It was done in 1852.
The drawing shows two girls by a window; these girls are probably the daughters of the artist. They are shown by a window facing [[Kongens Nytorv]] in [[Copenhagen]] but they are not watching anything on the square; they are reading a book.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.smk.dk/udforsk-kunsten/kunsthistorier/vaerker/vis/ved-et-vindue-i-kunstnerens-atelier-1852/ |title=At holde kaos på afstand|last1=Knudsen |first1=Vibeke Vibolt |last2= |first2= |date=2 February 2013 |work= |publisher=National Gallery of Denmark |accessdate=2 February 2013}}</ref>
