{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2014}} {{other people}} {{Infobox scientist |name = Einar Nilson Gjerstad |image = |image_size = |caption = |birth_date = {{birth date|1897|10|30|df=yes}} |birth_place = [[Örebro]], Sweden |death_date ={{death date and age|1988|01|08|1897|10|30|df=y}} |death_place =[[Lund]], Sweden |residence = |citizenship = |nationality = [[Sweden|Swedish]] |ethnicity = |field = [[Classical archaeology]] |work_institutions = The [[Swedish Institute at Rome]]; Lund University |alma_mater = Uppsala University |doctoral_advisor = Axel Persson |doctoral_students = |known_for = Study of [[Cypriot Bichrome ware]]; Early Rome |author_abbrev_bot = |author_abbrev_zoo = |influences = |influenced = |prizes = |religion = |footnotes = |signature = }}
'''Einar Nilson Gjerstad''' (30 October 1897, [[Örebro]] – 8 January 1988, [[Lund]]) was a [[Sweden|Swedish]] [[archaeologist]] of the ancient Mediterranean, particularly known for his work on [[Cyprus]],<ref name="Nison.)1926">{{cite book|author=Einar Gjerstad (Erik Paul Einar Nison.)|title=Studies on Prehistoric Cyprus. Inaug. Diss. by Einar Gjerstad|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ppByQwAACAAJ|year=1926|publisher=Uppsala universitets årsskrift, 1926.}}</ref> as well as his studies of early [[Rome]].<ref name="Gjerstad1966">{{cite book|author=Einar Gjerstad|title=Early Rome: Synthesis of archaeological evidence. 2 pts|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=iyRmAAAAMAAJ|year=1966|publisher=C. W. K. Gleerup}}</ref>
From 1927 until 1931 Gjerstad carried out excavations on Cyprus. From 1935 until 1940, Gjerstad served as director the [[Swedish Institute at Rome]]. When Gjerstad left Rome in 1940, he assumed the position of Professor of Classical Archaeology and Ancient History at Lund University.<ref>http://socialarchive.iath.virginia.edu/xtf/view?docId=gjerstad-einar-b-1897-cr.xml</ref>
He was a pioneer in the study of [[Cypriot Bichrome ware]].<ref name="1927-1931Gjerstad1972">{{cite book|author1=Svenska Cypernexpeditionen, 1927-1931|author2=Einar Gjerstad|author3=John Lindros |author4=Erik Sjöqvist |author5=Alfred Westholm|title=The Swedish Cyprus expedition: finds and results of the excavations in Cyprus, 1927-1931 ...|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=a2ltAAAAMAAJ|year=1972|publisher=The Swedish Cyprus Expedition}}</ref>
==Legacy== A street has been named after him in [[Larnaca]], Cyprus. (It is adjacent to the Bamboula archaeological site of [[Kition]].)
==Sources== *[http://archives2.getty.edu:8082/xtf/view?docId=ead/900228/900228.xml Einar Gjerstad research papers, 1806-1984] *"Einar Gjerstad," in ''A Historical Dictionary of Classical Archaeology'', ed. [[Nancy Thomson de Grummond|Nancy T. de Grummond]] (Greenwood Press, Westport, Connecticut 1996).
==Publications== * 1926 ''Studies on Prehistoric Cyprus'' * 1934 ''The Swedish Cyprus Expedition: Finds and Results of the Excavation in Cyprus 1927-1931. Vol. I'' * 1935 ''The Swedish Cyprus Expedition: Finds and Results of the Excavation in Cyprus 1927-1931. Vol. II'' * 1937 ''The Swedish Cyprus Expedition: Finds and Results of the Excavation in Cyprus 1927-1931. Vol. III'' * 1953 ''Early Rome Vol. I: Stratigraphical researches in the Forum Romanum and along the Sacra Via'' * 1956 ''Early Rome Vol. II: The tombs'' * 1960 ''Early Rome Vol. III: Fortifications, domestic architecture, sanctuaries, stratigraphic excavations'' * 1962 ''Legends and Facts of Early Roman History'' * 1966 ''Early Rome Vol. IV: Synthesis of archaeological evidence'' * 1973 ''Early Rome Vol. V: The written sources'' * 1973 ''Early Rome Vol. VI: Historical survey'' * 1980 ''Ages and Days in Cyprus'', Paul Åström, Göteborg.
